WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:06.400
Dominoes. Quick starter. Sherlock Holmes. The Dying Detective.

00:06.400 --> 00:10.720
By Sir Arthur Conan Doyle. Adapted by Leslie Thompson.

00:11.520 --> 00:18.400
Read by Deneka Fairman. Rob Fitch. Wayne Forrester. Roger May. And James Daniel Wilson.

00:19.520 --> 00:23.280
Published in Copyright Oxford University Press 2016.

00:23.280 --> 00:28.000
Chapter 1. Holmes is ill.

00:37.760 --> 00:50.400
It is 1890 in London. At 221B Baker Street. Mrs Hudson. Sherlock Holmes's servant is sad.

00:51.200 --> 01:03.840
Things are very bad. Holmes is dying. Three days now. And he is worse. She thinks.

01:05.680 --> 01:12.400
Mrs Hudson likes Holmes very much. But she is also a little afraid of him.

01:13.120 --> 01:22.960
He is different. He has strange visitors. And they come at all hours of the day and night.

01:24.720 --> 01:32.240
His rooms have many strange things in them. But he is very nice to Mrs Hudson.

01:32.960 --> 01:38.240
She respects him. And she does not want to lose him.

01:39.920 --> 01:46.720
I must visit Dr Watson. She thinks. He can help.

01:48.800 --> 01:54.800
At this time Dr Watson is living in a different street in London.

01:56.320 --> 01:59.280
Mrs Hudson goes quickly to his rooms.

02:00.160 --> 02:06.320
Dr Watson. She cries. When the doctor opens the door to her.

02:06.800 --> 02:13.600
Please come with me. It is Mr Holmes. He is dying.

02:14.640 --> 02:21.440
What? Watson cries. I know nothing about this.

02:22.400 --> 02:35.360
He doesn't want a doctor. But you must come sir. After three days he is very very ill.

02:36.480 --> 02:44.880
He is saying strange things. I am afraid for him. You must be quick.

02:45.840 --> 02:51.200
Watson gets his coat and bag. And they leave the house.

02:53.200 --> 02:58.240
In the cab he asks Mrs Hudson some more questions.

02:59.440 --> 03:02.000
I can't tell you much sir.

03:02.800 --> 03:08.400
Lately Mr Holmes is working in Rotherhive near the river.

03:09.360 --> 03:13.840
He comes home and he brings this illness with him.

03:14.880 --> 03:20.400
He is much worse now. Can he live through this?

03:32.560 --> 03:36.480
Chapter Two. Watson cannot help.

03:36.480 --> 03:52.400
When they arrive at Baker Street on that dark November day Holmes is alive.

03:53.680 --> 04:01.280
But Watson is afraid for his friend. The detective's face is yellow

04:02.240 --> 04:09.680
and his eyes are red with fever. His hands move without stopping.

04:10.960 --> 04:14.320
When he speaks his voice is weak.

04:15.520 --> 04:23.280
Well Watson bad days are here I think. He smiles weekly.

04:24.080 --> 04:31.680
My poor man cries Watson and he moves towards the bed.

04:32.720 --> 04:40.080
Don't come near me. But why? I only want to help.

04:41.200 --> 04:52.080
I know but you can't help me. My illness is from the far east and it's very contagious.

04:53.440 --> 05:02.160
I'm a doctor says Watson quietly. These things don't matter to me.

05:03.520 --> 05:12.720
Don't move and I can talk to you. If not you must leave the room now.

05:14.640 --> 05:19.360
Holmes looks at Watson with fever in his eyes.

05:20.320 --> 05:29.360
I can't trust you with this Watson. You know nothing of these strange illnesses.

05:30.640 --> 05:39.440
Do you know about tapa newly fever for example or the black formosa fever?

05:40.640 --> 05:45.440
No you don't. You aren't a specialist.

05:45.600 --> 05:52.880
I'm sorry to say this but I must see a specialist.

05:55.120 --> 06:02.400
Watson is not happy at these words but he also respects the detective.

06:04.080 --> 06:15.280
Very well Holmes. Dr Ainstree the best specialist in these illnesses is now in London.

06:16.400 --> 06:18.240
I'm going to him now.

06:20.800 --> 06:27.920
Watson walks towards the door. Suddenly Holmes is out of bed.

06:29.440 --> 06:39.600
He goes quickly to the door and locks it. Then he goes very slowly back to bed.

06:39.920 --> 06:48.480
What's and looks at his friend in shock. What is the matter with Holmes?

07:00.320 --> 07:05.600
Chapter three. Holmes is worse.

07:10.400 --> 07:17.200
Holmes cries excitedly.

07:18.240 --> 07:25.280
Stay here Watson. I've got the key. What time is it?

07:26.240 --> 07:33.360
Four o'clock. At six o'clock you can go but not before.

07:33.520 --> 07:46.320
What's and looks at his friend sadly. Holmes. This illness is doing strange things to your head.

07:47.680 --> 08:00.240
But I can wait until six. Good. One more thing Watson. Don't bring that man Ainstree.

08:01.120 --> 08:14.080
Now perhaps I can sleep a little. Watson waits looking at the pictures and books in the room.

08:15.600 --> 08:26.720
On a table he sees a little black and white box. Hmm that's interesting. He thinks.

08:27.680 --> 08:36.240
He moves his hand towards it. Suddenly a terrible cry comes from the bed.

08:37.040 --> 08:50.000
Stop Watson. Don't move my things. I don't like it. Sit down man. I need to sleep.

08:57.360 --> 09:11.840
At six o'clock Holmes says. Let's have some light Watson. But only a little. Put the box near me.

09:12.880 --> 09:19.440
And not with your hands. Use your handkerchief. That's right.

09:20.320 --> 09:33.280
Now you can go to Mr. Culverton Smith of Thirteen Lower Burke Street. But who is this man Holmes?

09:34.240 --> 09:46.480
I don't know the name. He isn't a doctor. He has a plantation in Sumatra but he's visiting London.

09:47.360 --> 09:59.760
He knows this illness well because his workers often have it. Things are not good between us.

10:01.200 --> 10:12.720
Smith's nephew Victor Savage is dead. There is something wrong about his terrible death.

10:13.600 --> 10:27.280
I don't trust Smith and he knows it. But only he can help me. There is one more thing.

10:28.560 --> 10:38.640
Don't come back with him. You must be here before him. This is very important Watson.

10:39.280 --> 10:49.840
Watson takes the key and he goes into the street. He sees Inspector Morton of Scotland Yard.

10:50.800 --> 11:05.680
How is Mr. Holmes, sir? Morton asks. He's very ill. Watson answers. Morton smiles strangely.

11:05.680 --> 11:21.680
I know something about it. He says. Watson doesn't understand. But he cannot wait. He gets into a cab and leaves.

11:35.680 --> 11:38.800
Chapter Four. The Specialist.

11:47.600 --> 11:57.360
At Thirteen Lower Burke Street, a servant answers the door. Watson goes into the house.

11:58.240 --> 12:11.120
He can hear Culverton Smith's voice. Oh, Ace, Watson. What does he want? I need to work. I cannot see him.

12:12.720 --> 12:18.880
Watson thinks of Holmes. Quickly, he goes into the room.

12:19.520 --> 12:31.280
The man in the room stands up from his chair. Watson sees his dark, angry eyes. What's this?

12:32.240 --> 12:44.160
The man cries. I'm sorry, says Watson. But I can't wait. It's about Mr. Sherlock Holmes.

12:44.560 --> 13:02.160
Colverton Smith's face changes. He watches Watson carefully. What about Holmes? How is he? He's very ill.

13:02.800 --> 13:26.160
Watson sits down. Is that a smile on Smith's face? I'm sorry to hear this. Smith says. I don't know Holmes well, but I respect him. We're not very different.

13:26.800 --> 13:39.520
He studies criminals, and I study microbes. He looks at the bottles on the table next to him and laughs.

13:43.520 --> 13:54.160
Holmes needs you. Watson says. Why? Is his illness from the Far East?

13:55.120 --> 14:10.960
Perhaps his work lately is with people from there. Oh, I see. Smith smiles. How many days is it now?

14:11.840 --> 14:24.880
About three? Is he thinking well? Not always. That is bad. I must go and help him.

14:26.800 --> 14:39.440
Watson remembers Holmes' words. He says, I can't go with you. I need to make a visit. Very well.

14:40.320 --> 14:51.600
Smith says, I can be there in half an hour.

14:51.920 --> 15:01.760
Chapter five. A killer at Baker Street.

15:02.720 --> 15:24.800
Watson runs into Holmes' room. Is he coming? Holmes asks. Yes, he is. Very good, Watson.

15:25.600 --> 15:37.920
Hmm. Now you must hide behind the bed. Don't speak or move. Just listen very carefully.

15:40.480 --> 15:51.040
Watson hides behind the bed and waits. Soon he hears Colvat and Smith's voice.

15:51.920 --> 16:08.560
Can you hear me, Holmes? Is that you, Mr. Smith? Holmes says weekly. Thank you for coming. Smith laughs.

16:09.200 --> 16:25.680
What's the matter with you, Holmes? It's Victor's illness, I think. Yes. My nephew. Four days ill and he's dead.

16:26.320 --> 16:42.960
Smith laughs again. And you are the criminal, Smith. But you can't prove it. And now you need me.

16:43.360 --> 16:56.320
Give me water. Holmes says weekly. All right. But only because I want to say something to you.

16:57.520 --> 17:08.560
Your illness is from men working near the river, your friend says. But that's wrong. You aren't

17:08.560 --> 17:23.760
very quick. Are you Holmes? I can't think. You must help me. Think carefully. Think about a box

17:23.760 --> 17:37.600
arriving here last Wednesday. A box. Yes. I remember now. The spring in the box

17:38.240 --> 17:51.520
on my hand. The blood. That's right. And there are microbes of your illness on that spring.

17:52.960 --> 18:07.200
This box is the only proof. And I'm taking it with me. Now you know the truth. Now you can.

18:07.600 --> 18:22.640
Die. More light says Holmes weekly. Smith moves. And suddenly there is more light in the room.

18:24.320 --> 18:32.240
What more can I do for you? Smith asks. And more water, please.

18:33.200 --> 18:45.200
Holmes says. But what is happening? Holmes is speaking normally. His voice is not weak.

18:46.000 --> 18:56.000
Watson hears this. And he nearly cries out. He can feel Culverton Smith's shock.

18:56.000 --> 19:11.360
Chapter six. The truth.

19:11.360 --> 19:34.400
What is this? Aren't you ill? Culverton Smith asks angrily. After three days without food or drink,

19:35.120 --> 19:45.680
I'm not very well. But I'm much better than you think. Holmes says in his normal voice.

19:46.640 --> 19:54.160
Ah. A friend is coming, I think. The light is telling him to come.

19:54.480 --> 20:07.040
The door opens. And Inspector Morton comes in. This is your man, Inspector. Holmes says.

20:07.040 --> 20:18.720
I arrest you for the murder of Victor Savage. Morton says to Smith. He wants my murder too.

20:19.680 --> 20:31.360
Holmes laughs. The proof is in the box in his coat. But don't put your hand on it, Inspector.

20:32.720 --> 20:38.400
Smith cries. You can't prove anything, Holmes.

20:39.280 --> 20:53.280
Don't forget my friend, Dr. Watson. Holmes says. He can tell an interesting story. Come out, Watson.

20:53.440 --> 21:05.040
Hmm. Morton leaves with Culverton Smith. Holmes dresses, and then he talks to Watson.

21:06.480 --> 21:20.320
I'm a good actor, Watson. And no food or drink for three days is easy for me. This yellow face

21:20.320 --> 21:32.880
is only makeup. You can't come near me and not see the truth. So my illness is contagious.

21:34.240 --> 21:45.280
Bad light in the room helps with my act. Victor Savage's murder is all about money.

21:46.160 --> 21:57.640
Money is more important than family to Culverton Smith. I get some strange things at this house.

21:57.640 --> 22:11.680
Happily, I always open them very carefully. Now we must go to Scotland Yard. After that,

22:11.680 --> 22:18.960
I want to sit down with you and eat until midnight.

